{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"6 circle silicone sphere mould , large bowl, large plate, bowl, pastry brush, refrigerator","id":"r138844","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-xTUhVthenPA\/XZWclC-L2WI\/AAAAAAAAebo\/rh6esNqr1NoOvE4uJzW-bgeQ1EmE_bw9QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1wjgKLAFMqFJqCpe.png","title":"Chocolate crackle surprise","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"250 g Copha, cut into 4 pieces (see Tips)"},{"content":"50 g desiccated coconut"},{"content":"50 g icing sugar"},{"content":"30 g cocoa powder"},{"content":"130 g crispy rice cereal (e.g. Rice Bubbles)"},{"content":"100 g milk chocolate chips"},{"content":"100 g lollies of choice (see Tips)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"3.4 g","fat":"35.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"33.6 g","calories":"1935 kJ \/ 461 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Set aside 6-hole silicone sphere moulds (6.5 cm)."},{"content":"Place Copha into mixing bowl and heat <b>8-10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, until completely melted. Allow to cool slightly in mixing bowl (approx. 5 minutes)."},{"content":"Add coconut, icing sugar and cocoa powder and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add rice cereal and combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Transfer mixture into a large bowl."},{"content":"Place 2 tablespoons of the mixture into each mould. Working quickly, use your finger tips or the back of a spoon to press mixture around all sides of the mould, right to the edge of the mould. Transfer moulds into refrigerator to set (approx. 10-15 minutes). Carefully unmould crackles and transfer onto a large plate, then place into refrigerator until needed."},{"content":"Using spatula, stir chocolate mixture to ensure Copha is evenly distributed. Place 2 tablespoons of the mixture into each mould. Working quickly, use your finger tips or the back of a spoon to press mixture around all sides of the mould, right to the edge of the mould. Transfer moulds into refrigerator to set (approx. 10-15 minutes). Carefully unmould crackles and transfer onto a large plate, then place into refrigerator until needed."},{"content":"Using spatula, stir chocolate mixture to ensure Copha is evenly distributed. Place 2 tablespoons of the mixture into each mould. Working quickly, use your finger tips or the back of a spoon to press mixture around all sides of the mould, right to the edge of the mould. Transfer moulds into refrigerator to set (approx. 10-15 minutes). Carefully unmould crackles and transfer onto a large plate, then place into refrigerator until needed. Recipe makes a total of 18 semi-circles. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place chocolate chips into mixing bowl and heat <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and heat <b>1 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b> or until melted. Transfer into a shallow bowl."},{"content":"Fill half of the crackle semi-circles with lollies of choice. Carefully brush edges of the remaining 9 semi-circles with the melted chocolate, then join the lolly-filled semi-circles and press together gently to seal and form a ball. Transfer into refrigerator to set for 1 hour (see Tips)."},{"content":"Serve crackle surprises as party favours."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Copha is a solid vegetable shortening, and can be found at most major supermarkets in the refrigerated section.","Crackle surprises can be stored in the refrigerator in an airtight container for 1 week.","You can fill with small chocolates, jelly beans, or even a small toy.","<strong>Chocolate crackles<\/strong>: Place 1-2 tablespoons of crackle mixture into base of cupcake liners. Transfer into a sealable container and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","2h 30m","9 portions"]}